Firm commitments and forecast transactions relate to transactions for which a legally binding contract was concluded but not yet performed on by either contracting party, as well as contingent payment claims for already partially completed performance obligations in the project and product businesses.

As of September 30, 2023, the fair value of derivative financial instruments from foreign currency hedging transactions was €(4) million, net. Positive fair values of €1,897 million were offset by negative fair values of €1,901 million. For derivative financial instruments with negative fair values, no provision for anticipated losses was recognized as part of the valuation unit.